        <property propertyId="67f102e2-9cb6-4d20-aa16-bf74d8a03326" amount="1.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">wet mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. According to HERA report on Alkyl Sulphate (2002) the EU consumes 102 thousand tonnes per year of which around 65% are C12 to C14. The global production volume is extrapolated from the European one based on the following asssumptions.

According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3,534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (USA, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the USA total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 
The European production volume is extrapolated from the global production volume, which was estimated for 2001 in Pakalin et al. (2007). to be 56.1 thousand metric tonnes, using the shares reported above for EU28 plus other Europe, therefore a share of 14.7% + 2.7% = 17.4%.


Reference(s):
Pakalin, S. et al. 2007.  “REVIEW ON PRODUCTION PROCESSES OF DECABROMODIPHENYL ETHER (DECABDE) USED IN POLYMERIC APPLICATIONS IN ELECTRICAL AND ELECTRONIC EQUIPMENT, AND ASSESSMENT OF THE AVAILABILITY OF POTENTIAL ALTERNATIVES TO DECABDE'. EUROPEAN COMMISSION, European Communities, Italy.
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/, accessed 1 June 2017
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html, accessed 1 June 2017
HERA 2002. HERA focused environmental risk assessment of Alkyl Sulphate. Retrieved from: http://www.heraproject.com/files/3-E-417F36A9-DB35-F780-97A4CF8B60763C35.pdf, accessed 1 August 2017</productionVolumeComment>
