      <intermediateExchange id="d881cf69-e069-5955-8ed6-86d07044c6a6" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="1310-73-2" amount="0.012987816461163995" intermediateExchangeId="61396bcb-bf35-411a-a6a6-8543ccef83e8" activityLinkId="0ff14b6a-8dcf-508f-a340-73733d530fd5">
        <name xml:lang="en">sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
39.997108g/mol is the molar mass of sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state (HNaO). 
288.383868g/mol is the molar mass of alkyl sulphate (C12-14) (NaC12H25SO4). 

Alkyl sulphates are here produced from a mix of C12-14 fatty alcohol oleo (hydrogenation of fatty acids and methyl esters) and petro based (produced from the Ziegler process). Fatty alcohols are esterified with sulfur trioxide. Sodium hydroxide is then used to neutralize the product (Kosswig 2012).
Chemical reaction:
C12H26O + SO3 + NaOH -&gt; NaC12H25SO4 + H2O
</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.012987816461163995" mu="-4.343743556257771" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.010025"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="2" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
        </uncertainty>
